1
00:00:06,128 --> 00:00:08,240
I don't care if it will be months, or years,

2
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:09,342
or all my life,

3
00:00:09,402 --> 00:00:11,640
I will wait for you and you only

4
00:00:12,352 --> 00:00:13,353
forever.

5
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:17,440
If you saw us, then you would know

6
00:00:17,547 --> 00:00:18,920
that we love each other.

7
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:20,700
The prince and I, we are in love.

8
00:00:20,712 --> 00:00:24,120
- You shouldn't dragged the sky to the ground level.
- If it got in my way,

9
00:00:24,648 --> 00:00:26,560
if to be a master and a servant got in my way,

10
00:00:27,272 --> 00:00:28,840
I will destroy them all.

11
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:45,212
Your Highness!

12
00:00:45,598 --> 00:00:46,599
Dad!

13
00:02:17,306 --> 00:02:18,730
Put on your clothes now.

14
00:02:19,690 --> 00:02:20,850
And go back to your room.

15
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,490
I said go! Now!

16
00:02:38,370 --> 00:02:39,890
What did you do to my son?

17
00:02:44,371 --> 00:02:46,130
It's my fault, my own fault.

18
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:48,710
Please punish only me.

19
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:52,730
I was kind to you. I gave you great opportunities.

20
00:02:53,901 --> 00:02:56,338
You got to study in higher level than the servants could.

21
00:02:56,498 --> 00:02:58,250
This is how to repay me?

22
00:03:02,258 --> 00:03:03,450
What did I do wrong?

23
00:03:04,970 --> 00:03:06,330
I just love him.

24
00:03:08,427 --> 00:03:10,440
Stop with your smart mouth already!

25
00:03:11,170 --> 00:03:14,650
A servant like you has nothing to lose!

26
00:03:15,909 --> 00:03:19,050
You don't have to worry about being another piece of scandal.

27
00:03:19,837 --> 00:03:21,210
But my son has to.

28
00:03:21,415 --> 00:03:23,710
We have pride and dignity.

29
00:03:27,490 --> 00:03:29,970
There is no status in love.

30
00:03:30,194 --> 00:03:32,810
It doesn't care about your origins or genders.

31
00:03:34,008 --> 00:03:36,290
My love has dignity too.

32
00:03:38,466 --> 00:03:41,050
A servant's dignity has no value.

33
00:03:41,450 --> 00:03:43,710
You can't compare it to us.

34
00:03:44,270 --> 00:03:45,890
What did you do to my son?

35
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:47,931
What were you thinking?

36
00:03:55,510 --> 00:03:56,890
What did you do?

37
00:03:57,701 --> 00:04:00,010
Please don't hurt him, please.

38
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:04,110
Please don't hurt Phob, Dad.

39
00:04:05,818 --> 00:04:06,819
Let me go.

40
00:04:07,140 --> 00:04:08,410
Go back to your room!

41
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:12,650
Go! I told you to leave!

42
00:04:15,509 --> 00:04:16,510
You need to leave

43
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:19,330
or I will kill him.

44
00:04:40,653 --> 00:04:43,450
You need to get the hell out of my palace

45
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:46,170
before I lose my control

46
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:48,290
and get some blood out of your skull.

47
00:04:49,690 --> 00:04:51,730
Don't ever show your face back here again.

48
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:53,770
Get out!

49
00:05:38,648 --> 00:05:39,649
Dad?

50
00:05:44,458 --> 00:05:46,170
Did you do anything to Phob?

51
00:05:49,872 --> 00:05:52,050
Please tell me that you didn't do anything to him

52
00:05:52,110 --> 00:05:53,210
after I left.

53
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:02,850
You didn't hurt him more than that, did you?

54
00:06:04,853 --> 00:06:05,854
Get up.

55
00:06:06,410 --> 00:06:09,610
Dad, tell me!

56
00:06:11,290 --> 00:06:13,610
Can you please tell me?

57
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:17,890
Tell me first.

58
00:06:21,570 --> 00:06:23,410
What did you do to him?

59
00:06:30,722 --> 00:06:31,723
Get up.

60
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:41,860
You didn't hurt him, did you?

61
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,570
Please, just tell me.

62
00:06:47,770 --> 00:06:48,771
Please.

63
00:07:00,237 --> 00:07:01,330
I will pretend that

64
00:07:04,712 --> 00:07:06,690
nothing happens tonight,

65
00:07:08,418 --> 00:07:09,610
and so should you.

66
00:07:10,874 --> 00:07:13,050
Nobody can hear about it.

67
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,890
It will be our secret for the rest of our lives.

68
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:20,050
What about Phob?

69
00:07:20,194 --> 00:07:21,195
Listen to me.

70
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,050
You are the one and only hope

71
00:07:26,344 --> 00:07:28,530
of our family.

72
00:07:29,096 --> 00:07:30,250
Do you understand me?

73
00:07:34,088 --> 00:07:35,250
Understand?

74
00:07:37,314 --> 00:07:38,315
Yes, sir.

75
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,170
Chat is useless.

76
00:07:42,256 --> 00:07:43,650
He is unreliable.

77
00:07:44,837 --> 00:07:46,250
You are the only one

78
00:07:47,232 --> 00:07:49,730
who can take care of our family.

79
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:52,310
I have no one left.

80
00:07:55,872 --> 00:07:58,490
It would have been better if you weren't my son.

81
00:08:00,653 --> 00:08:01,654
Dad?

82
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:05,171
But you…

83
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:09,130
are Mom Chao Tinnakorn Varakulvatin.

84
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:12,650
You were born to be a prince

85
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,730
and you can't change this fact.

86
00:08:23,632 --> 00:08:24,731
I'm sorry.

87
00:08:27,712 --> 00:08:30,610
I don't want to hurt your feeling like this.

88
00:08:36,448 --> 00:08:37,810
I love you.

89
00:08:41,650 --> 00:08:43,570
You understand me, don't you?

90
00:09:37,621 --> 00:09:38,890
Tin! Tin! Tin!

91
00:09:40,402 --> 00:09:42,850
What happened last night? Why did Phob come back?

92
00:09:43,085 --> 00:09:44,445
Why? Why was he here?

93
00:09:44,504 --> 00:09:47,210
What? Phob was here last night?

94
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:48,891
Where is he now?

95
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:50,251
Dad?

96
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:53,410
What happened last night? What troubles did Phob bring?

97
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:02,130
This name is forbidden in this house.

98
00:10:02,594 --> 00:10:04,450
You can't ask me about it again.

99
00:10:32,648 --> 00:10:34,882
I don't care if it will be months, or years,

100
00:10:35,245 --> 00:10:36,250
or all my life,

101
00:10:37,314 --> 00:10:39,530
I will wait for you and you only.

102
00:10:41,554 --> 00:10:43,570
No matter what,

103
00:10:44,450 --> 00:10:45,451
I will forever

104
00:10:46,451 --> 00:10:47,452
be your Phob.

105
00:10:50,090 --> 00:10:52,770
It would have been better if you weren't my son.

106
00:10:53,210 --> 00:10:54,330
But you…

107
00:10:55,170 --> 00:10:58,330
are Mom Chao Tinnakorn Varakulvatin.

108
00:10:59,434 --> 00:11:01,650
You were born to be a prince

109
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:04,710
and you can't change this fact.

110
00:11:08,986 --> 00:11:11,890
I don't want to hurt your feeling like this.

111
00:11:13,090 --> 00:11:14,370
I love you.

112
00:11:18,437 --> 00:11:20,210
You understand me, don't you?

113
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,570
Give it to me.

114
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:59,050
Phob, is it okay?

115
00:12:07,658 --> 00:12:08,659
What about these two?

116
00:12:47,610 --> 00:12:50,410
Hurry up, guys. Come on.

117
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,081
Don't drop it.

118
00:12:53,370 --> 00:12:54,371
Bring them to the car.

119
00:12:54,677 --> 00:12:55,678
Hurry up.

120
00:13:09,389 --> 00:13:10,390
Tin,

121
00:13:12,834 --> 00:13:14,898
I hope you know how to behave properly

122
00:13:15,505 --> 00:13:16,530
from now on.

123
00:13:27,858 --> 00:13:29,010
Focus on your study

124
00:13:29,814 --> 00:13:32,570
and forget everything.

125
00:13:34,568 --> 00:13:36,010
Can you promise me that?

126
00:13:38,884 --> 00:13:39,885
Yes, sir.

127
00:13:41,130 --> 00:13:42,410
I know it well that

128
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:44,770
I'm not just a guy named Tinnakorn

129
00:13:46,252 --> 00:13:48,650
but I am everything to Varakulvatin.

130
00:13:55,330 --> 00:13:56,331
Thank you, son.

131
00:13:59,141 --> 00:14:00,142
Thank you so much.

132
00:14:17,341 --> 00:14:18,342
You should go.

133
00:14:22,802 --> 00:14:24,090
Please take care of it for me.

134
00:15:10,685 --> 00:15:11,686
Dear Phob,

135
00:15:13,421 --> 00:15:16,530
I've been thinking a lot whether I should write this letter.

136
00:15:19,141 --> 00:15:22,210
And I'm not sure how you would feel after reading this.

137
00:15:24,106 --> 00:15:25,850
What happened between us

138
00:15:26,992 --> 00:15:28,210
is entirely my fault.

139
00:15:30,110 --> 00:15:32,949
It could be the fact that we grew up together

140
00:15:34,594 --> 00:15:35,810
and we were so close that

141
00:15:36,701 --> 00:15:40,090
we misunderstood our bond as love.

142
00:15:42,096 --> 00:15:43,890
When I finally came to my senses,

143
00:15:45,088 --> 00:15:46,732
I realized that what happened between us

144
00:15:47,213 --> 00:15:49,930
was just a kid's foolishness who didn't know anything better.

145
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:53,730
We should forget everything

146
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:56,260
and leave it as it should be

147
00:15:57,117 --> 00:15:58,850
for everyone's benefits,

148
00:15:59,530 --> 00:16:00,850
especially for you.

149
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:05,770
I don't want your future to be tainted because of this.

150
00:16:08,893 --> 00:16:10,130
From now on,

151
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:14,130
I will try my best to fulfill my duties,

152
00:16:15,304 --> 00:16:18,430
and I want you to live your life the way you're meant to.

153
00:16:21,573 --> 00:16:23,010
Please forget about me.

154
00:16:24,361 --> 00:16:25,490
Best regards, Tinnakorn,

155
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:28,850
your old pal.

156
00:17:05,584 --> 00:17:06,710
[Will people gain freedom or simply changing new boss?]

157
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,310
[Officials need to stay strong, be struggle like the citizens. ]

158
00:17:08,570 --> 00:17:09,730
[11 Years Later]

159
00:17:10,690 --> 00:17:13,330
[1931, Siam]

160
00:17:38,709 --> 00:17:40,450
The party is turned out to be spectacular, Your Highness.

161
00:17:41,328 --> 00:17:43,130
It was because you were helping to organize it,

162
00:17:43,510 --> 00:17:45,330
that's why it went smoothly like this.

163
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:48,530
Our economy is in bad shape right now

164
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:52,317
but we organized such a big event. The newspaper

165
00:17:53,128 --> 00:17:54,129
could attack on us tomorrow.

166
00:17:55,710 --> 00:17:57,450
The leftists are criticizing everything

167
00:17:57,926 --> 00:17:59,410
and they are getting worse day by day.

168
00:18:00,325 --> 00:18:02,250
Some of them are asking for regime change.

169
00:18:04,941 --> 00:18:06,110
How could it be transformed?

170
00:18:06,765 --> 00:18:08,892
Our country is nothing like the western countries.

171
00:18:09,186 --> 00:18:10,610
Please don't mind them.

172
00:18:12,890 --> 00:18:15,330
Ms. Siri, please follow me this way.

173
00:18:16,890 --> 00:18:17,891
This way, please.

174
00:18:25,154 --> 00:18:26,155
Oh my,

175
00:18:27,370 --> 00:18:29,110
did you see that solider?

176
00:18:30,290 --> 00:18:33,010
The good-looking one?

177
00:18:33,341 --> 00:18:35,730
I heard that he was a scholar, studied in France.

178
00:18:37,176 --> 00:18:38,177
He's so handsome.

179
00:19:47,970 --> 00:19:50,490
You and Captain Phobthee know each other?

180
00:19:52,533 --> 00:19:53,534
Captain?

181
00:19:55,010 --> 00:19:56,011
Captain Phobthee

182
00:19:57,370 --> 00:19:59,490
this is Prince Tinnakorn Varakulvatin.

183
00:19:59,829 --> 00:20:00,970
He is His Majesty's Principal Private Secretary.

184
00:20:02,688 --> 00:20:03,689
Your Highness,

185
00:20:04,778 --> 00:20:06,690
this is Captain Phobthee Munkongphak,

186
00:20:08,461 --> 00:20:10,370
a representative from army's Artillery Division.

187
00:20:14,866 --> 00:20:16,252
Nice to meet you,

188
00:20:17,586 --> 00:20:18,587
Prince Tinnakorn.

189
00:20:20,493 --> 00:20:21,494
You too.

190
00:20:22,018 --> 00:20:23,410
It's nice to meet you.

191
00:20:25,504 --> 00:20:28,370
Captain Phobthee was a scholarship student to study in France.

192
00:20:29,162 --> 00:20:31,210
He was the top student of his class.

193
00:20:31,710 --> 00:20:33,170
He has a bright future ahead for sure.

194
00:20:39,496 --> 00:20:41,010
I am just a son of commoners.

195
00:20:44,672 --> 00:20:46,330
But someone once taught me that

196
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:51,532
people should live their lives the way they're meant to.

197
00:20:54,410 --> 00:20:55,610
That's why I was trying so hard,

198
00:20:56,411 --> 00:20:58,450
and striving to be where I am today.

199
00:21:04,610 --> 00:21:05,710
Excuse me,

200
00:21:07,810 --> 00:21:08,811
Your Highness.

201
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:18,530
I wondered where you were.

202
00:22:18,930 --> 00:22:21,050
- To get your favorite drink.
- Thank you. Cheers.

203
00:22:27,592 --> 00:22:28,593
Refreshing.

204
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,770
- You're right.
- Nice smell too.

205
00:22:40,408 --> 00:22:41,890
Who is he?

206
00:22:42,450 --> 00:22:43,451
Your friend?

207
00:22:44,882 --> 00:22:46,250
No, he's not.

208
00:22:46,856 --> 00:22:48,857
He's not someone that I know.

209
00:22:50,730 --> 00:22:52,490
We should go inside.

210
00:23:01,861 --> 00:23:03,330
Our country is in distress,

211
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:06,650
but a fundraising event is pretentiously extravagant.

212
00:23:07,090 --> 00:23:08,410
This is ridiculous.

213
00:23:08,616 --> 00:23:11,010
When I wrote about it in the newspaper,

214
00:23:11,170 --> 00:23:12,570
they thought that I was sarcastic.

215
00:23:14,850 --> 00:23:16,851
This is the first time that I met

216
00:23:16,997 --> 00:23:19,290
Prince Tinnakorn, the royal secretary.

217
00:23:20,026 --> 00:23:21,810
He is so good-looking

218
00:23:22,021 --> 00:23:24,250
like people have said.

219
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:29,330
He seems to be the perfect match for his fiancée, named….

220
00:23:31,290 --> 00:23:32,330
What is her name?

221
00:23:35,581 --> 00:23:36,582
Ruethaisiri.

222
00:23:42,157 --> 00:23:44,210
You lived in Varakulvatin Palace when you were a kid.

223
00:23:45,624 --> 00:23:47,290
How was Prince Tinnakorn when he was young?

224
00:23:47,970 --> 00:23:49,971
Has he always been this good-looking?

225
00:24:11,530 --> 00:24:13,450
- What do you think?
- I'll keep going.

226
00:24:15,610 --> 00:24:16,930
- Come to me.
- Wait.

227
00:24:17,930 --> 00:24:18,931
It's straight for me.

228
00:24:25,082 --> 00:24:26,130
It's not fun anymore.

229
00:24:32,138 --> 00:24:33,970
Where are you rushing to, sir?

230
00:24:34,202 --> 00:24:37,050
- But I…
- Well, you're Prince Chatthorn,

231
00:24:37,410 --> 00:24:40,450
we can loan you some money, just give me the number.

232
00:24:41,034 --> 00:24:42,250
Come on, let's continue.

233
00:24:42,715 --> 00:24:43,716
This way, sir.

234
00:24:44,005 --> 00:24:45,770
Come on, follow me.

235
00:24:49,312 --> 00:24:50,570
Have a seat, sir.

236
00:24:54,642 --> 00:24:56,210
Take care of him, okay.

237
00:24:57,037 --> 00:24:59,130
Enjoy yourself.

238
00:25:02,490 --> 00:25:04,930
- Let's continue.
- Go on!

239
00:25:09,210 --> 00:25:10,290
So sweet.

240
00:25:15,424 --> 00:25:17,010
[Favor nepo baby and firing commoners]

241
00:25:17,282 --> 00:25:19,710
Not fair to us!

242
00:25:27,610 --> 00:25:28,611
This is not fair!

243
00:25:28,944 --> 00:25:31,370
We've been working for the government for more than 10 years.

244
00:25:31,634 --> 00:25:34,290
And now you're firing us to maintain the balance?

245
00:25:34,328 --> 00:25:37,810
- Not fair!
- [Siam will be doomed because of trashy noblemen!]

246
00:25:38,402 --> 00:25:39,890
Siam will be in big trouble for sure.

247
00:25:40,632 --> 00:25:42,530
Not fair!

248
00:25:59,570 --> 00:26:01,852
Phob! You little servant!

249
00:26:02,584 --> 00:26:03,970
You!

250
00:26:09,330 --> 00:26:10,850
I am Captain Phobtheee

251
00:26:11,416 --> 00:26:13,050
from Artillery Division.

252
00:26:13,690 --> 00:26:15,691
I am representing the division and I'm here to ask for clarity

253
00:26:16,085 --> 00:26:18,570
about pension payment for junior rank soldiers.

254
00:26:19,770 --> 00:26:21,250
Captain? Really?

255
00:26:21,930 --> 00:26:25,010
I've never thought that you could push yourself to this level.

256
00:26:28,045 --> 00:26:29,650
I've never thought either that

257
00:26:31,090 --> 00:26:33,450
a person who kept failing classes like you

258
00:26:34,536 --> 00:26:37,137
would be working as the assistant to director-general of finance ministry.

259
00:26:39,672 --> 00:26:40,673
No wonder why

260
00:26:41,432 --> 00:26:43,050
- there're problems in budget.
- Phob!

261
00:26:45,693 --> 00:26:48,730
Don't you ever think that just because you're a soldier

262
00:26:48,898 --> 00:26:50,370
and you can be at the same level as me.

263
00:26:52,170 --> 00:26:54,570
You must have been trying so hard

264
00:26:54,869 --> 00:26:56,050
to become who you are now.

265
00:26:56,650 --> 00:26:59,317
Still, you're just a servant to me.

266
00:27:01,290 --> 00:27:02,570
You're so right.

267
00:27:03,472 --> 00:27:04,940
I've been trying so hard to be here.

268
00:27:06,170 --> 00:27:07,210
Unlike someone

269
00:27:07,910 --> 00:27:10,490
- who needs his daddy's favoritism.
- Phob!

270
00:27:17,191 --> 00:27:18,530
Long time no see.

271
00:27:20,230 --> 00:27:21,890
You're so bold,

272
00:27:22,850 --> 00:27:24,250
Captain Phobthee.

273
00:27:26,607 --> 00:27:29,130
Time changes, people change, sir.

274
00:27:30,506 --> 00:27:31,650
I hope that next time

275
00:27:32,469 --> 00:27:34,610
you will finish on reimbursement matter

276
00:27:34,874 --> 00:27:36,310
that hasn't been paid for months.

277
00:27:44,821 --> 00:27:45,822
Right,

278
00:27:49,110 --> 00:27:51,570
please send my regards to Prince Tinnakorn.

279
00:27:53,525 --> 00:27:55,530
We met the other night at the party. We were so busy

280
00:27:56,722 --> 00:27:58,733
that we didn't have a chance to chat about our past.

281
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:16,290
Didn't you see his eyes when he looked at me?

282
00:28:16,490 --> 00:28:18,610
How that low-rank soldier looked at me?

283
00:28:18,717 --> 00:28:20,770
He accused you of helping me with the job.

284
00:28:20,850 --> 00:28:22,851
What's wrong?

285
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:24,450
- Why are you yelling?
- Grandma.

286
00:28:24,488 --> 00:28:26,370
- It's about Phob.
- Why?

287
00:28:26,410 --> 00:28:27,890
He is now a Captain in military.

288
00:28:28,776 --> 00:28:31,890
- What? Good for him.
- Grandma!

289
00:28:32,093 --> 00:28:33,094
Don't compliment him.

290
00:28:33,224 --> 00:28:35,050
- What?
- He's so arrogant.

291
00:28:35,165 --> 00:28:36,450
He keeps on showing off his title around.

292
00:28:36,906 --> 00:28:39,110
He didin't show any respect to both of us.

293
00:28:39,130 --> 00:28:40,690
Hey! Stop whining already.

294
00:28:41,946 --> 00:28:44,530
You need to take care of the soldiers' reimbursement

295
00:28:44,922 --> 00:28:47,850
so he couldn't drag you into a mess, so embarrassing.

296
00:28:51,696 --> 00:28:52,697
Yes, sir.

297
00:29:14,338 --> 00:29:15,339
Tin.

298
00:29:16,930 --> 00:29:17,931
Yeah?

299
00:29:19,488 --> 00:29:20,489
We need to talk.

300
00:29:26,730 --> 00:29:28,330
You met Phob, didn't he?

301
00:29:30,354 --> 00:29:32,650
Yes, at the party.

302
00:29:34,924 --> 00:29:36,450
But you can tust me.

303
00:29:37,130 --> 00:29:38,450
I won't cause any trouble.

304
00:29:41,710 --> 00:29:43,050
Of course, I trust you.

305
00:29:43,946 --> 00:29:46,490
I know that you know what is right and wrong.

306
00:29:48,130 --> 00:29:49,650
It's somebody else that I don't trust.

307
00:29:51,405 --> 00:29:52,610
If you're talking about Phob,

308
00:29:54,184 --> 00:29:55,530
don't worry about him.

309
00:29:57,578 --> 00:29:58,810
He must have hated me already.

310
00:30:00,346 --> 00:30:01,930
What happened between me and Phob

311
00:30:02,942 --> 00:30:04,210
ended that night already.

312
00:30:41,613 --> 00:30:42,614
I love you.

313
00:30:45,874 --> 00:30:47,130
I love you, too.

314
00:31:15,994 --> 00:31:17,250
If you're talking about Phob,

315
00:31:20,010 --> 00:31:21,370
don't worry about him.

316
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:23,650
He must have hated me already.

317
00:31:24,608 --> 00:31:26,070
What happened between me and Phob

318
00:31:26,186 --> 00:31:27,570
ended that night already.

319
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:33,130
That night?

320
00:31:35,765 --> 00:31:38,210
It must be the night that Phob came to see Tin.

321
00:31:40,570 --> 00:31:41,571
Is that…

322
00:31:42,042 --> 00:31:43,043
Phob?

323
00:31:44,370 --> 00:31:46,010
What happened that night?

324
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,250
What did the students from France who came back

325
00:31:53,730 --> 00:31:56,410
at the same time as you say about this?

326
00:31:57,608 --> 00:31:59,330
They agreed that if we don't do something,

327
00:32:00,290 --> 00:32:02,530
people will become more struggling.

328
00:32:04,714 --> 00:32:06,130
We need to follow our plan

329
00:32:06,688 --> 00:32:07,970
like we discussed when we were there.

330
00:32:11,722 --> 00:32:14,930
The noble people are living their lives if nothing happens

331
00:32:15,410 --> 00:32:16,610
when people are in crisis like this.

332
00:32:17,970 --> 00:32:19,290
People start to question about the government

333
00:32:20,258 --> 00:32:23,170
that who are they ruling for?

334
00:32:26,205 --> 00:32:28,730
I will write a piece about people's dissatisfaction,

335
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:31,290
that they're done with being taken advantage of like this.

336
00:32:31,701 --> 00:32:33,330
You need to be careful.

337
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:36,890
There are people who will not be pleased with your work, Janthorn.

338
00:32:39,010 --> 00:32:40,370
If they are not pleased,

339
00:32:40,930 --> 00:32:43,290
it means that they are taking advantage of people.

340
00:32:45,026 --> 00:32:47,050
Just like what you are doing now.

341
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:49,410
People who disagree with my piece

342
00:32:49,965 --> 00:32:51,610
are someone who lose benefits from it.

343
00:32:53,778 --> 00:32:55,650
We need to be careful.

344
00:32:56,157 --> 00:32:57,250
I heard that

345
00:32:57,896 --> 00:32:59,810
the royal family members and noble people

346
00:33:01,218 --> 00:33:02,810
are watching progressives closely.

347
00:33:03,709 --> 00:33:05,810
I heard the same rumor as you.

348
00:33:06,178 --> 00:33:09,810
I also heard that they wore blue mark as their symbol.

349
00:33:15,021 --> 00:33:16,210
Blue mark?

350
00:33:42,013 --> 00:33:43,014
What did you say?

351
00:33:43,768 --> 00:33:45,690
Some people who are working for Lok Siam newspaper

352
00:33:45,710 --> 00:33:47,810
were a part of Palace Revolt of 1912's rebels?

353
00:33:48,333 --> 00:33:50,130
I just heard about it also.

354
00:33:50,621 --> 00:33:53,290
That's why they keep on attacking the government.

355
00:33:57,389 --> 00:34:00,210
Our late King was so kind and didn't order to execute them.

356
00:34:00,861 --> 00:34:03,110
And they didn't show their gratitude at all.

357
00:34:03,448 --> 00:34:05,010
Instead, they are seeking for the regime change.

358
00:34:05,565 --> 00:34:07,490
They are so ungratful to their own country.

359
00:34:07,629 --> 00:34:09,290
And they are working everywhere

360
00:34:09,512 --> 00:34:12,090
we need to keep an eye on them.

361
00:34:12,765 --> 00:34:14,690
I feel so relieved when I visit ministries

362
00:34:14,829 --> 00:34:17,410
and see people who are wearing the blue mark, our symbol,

363
00:34:17,490 --> 00:34:18,970
to help observing the opposite side.

364
00:34:23,890 --> 00:34:26,450
We need to protect our nation's main pillar,

365
00:34:26,694 --> 00:34:28,490
nobody can destroy it.

366
00:34:37,037 --> 00:34:38,050
The upcoming celebration

367
00:34:38,365 --> 00:34:40,770
is the significant event of the nation.

368
00:34:41,176 --> 00:34:42,482
I wish all parties

369
00:34:42,696 --> 00:34:44,970
to work on it carefully.

370
00:34:46,557 --> 00:34:49,000
Mr. Secretary, if we're all ready,

371
00:34:49,218 --> 00:34:51,219
please start with the meeting agenda now.

372
00:35:08,850 --> 00:35:11,930
I am Captain Phobtheee from Artillery Division.

373
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:14,890
I was assigned to be in charge of arranging soldiers

374
00:35:15,237 --> 00:35:16,730
and security team for

375
00:35:17,066 --> 00:35:20,110
the 150th Anniversary of Rattanakosin's celebration.

376
00:35:20,770 --> 00:35:23,810
Right, are you working for Mr. Kitti?

377
00:35:24,724 --> 00:35:27,210
I've heard a lot about you.

378
00:35:27,682 --> 00:35:28,970
About your job,

379
00:35:29,224 --> 00:35:31,722
I'd like to assign Mr. Secretary

380
00:35:32,373 --> 00:35:36,450
to coordinate with you directly.

381
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:39,011
Please have a seat.

382
00:35:41,285 --> 00:35:44,010
Mr. Secretary, please start.

383
00:35:49,026 --> 00:35:50,610
I'd like to start with the first agenda

384
00:35:50,710 --> 00:35:53,250
about our duties and coordination.

385
00:35:53,413 --> 00:35:56,810
It requires all parties to work together closely.

386
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,841
Hey.

387
00:36:15,250 --> 00:36:16,410
I'm here to remind you that

388
00:36:17,456 --> 00:36:19,770
when you're done with the minutes of meeting,

389
00:36:20,410 --> 00:36:21,570
please send it to me.

390
00:36:23,487 --> 00:36:24,488
Sure.

391
00:36:24,810 --> 00:36:27,650
When my team is done with it, I'll send it to you.

392
00:36:32,146 --> 00:36:33,147
Thank you.

393
00:37:51,976 --> 00:37:52,977
Thank you.

394
00:38:10,490 --> 00:38:11,930
You're acting as if I am that disgusting.

395
00:38:16,076 --> 00:38:17,730
I didn't do such thing, Mr. Phobthee.

396
00:38:19,519 --> 00:38:20,810
How could I dislike you?

397
00:38:21,530 --> 00:38:22,610
Look at you now.

398
00:38:25,045 --> 00:38:27,370
You're a soldier with a bright future.

399
00:38:36,170 --> 00:38:37,610
Someone once told me that

400
00:38:39,690 --> 00:38:41,050
people's status

401
00:38:41,872 --> 00:38:43,290
can be different based on their competency.

402
00:38:44,602 --> 00:38:45,810
He also told me that

403
00:38:46,965 --> 00:38:49,130
he believed in me.

404
00:38:52,490 --> 00:38:55,650
That keeps me motivated and working hard until now.

405
00:38:58,130 --> 00:39:00,650
Your achievements come from your own ability,

406
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:03,890
it's not because of the nonsense word of encouragement.

407
00:39:06,309 --> 00:39:07,310
Nonsense?

408
00:39:10,205 --> 00:39:11,206
You're right, I guess.

409
00:39:13,069 --> 00:39:16,130
The speaker may not feel anything.

410
00:39:17,352 --> 00:39:19,530
It's just a word full of lies and meaningless.

411
00:39:22,093 --> 00:39:23,810
Then you should forget about it already.

412
00:39:24,877 --> 00:39:26,770
Don't focus on some random and useless word.

413
00:39:34,250 --> 00:39:35,450
Can you teach me

414
00:39:36,274 --> 00:39:38,632
how to stop your feeling, be ruthless

415
00:39:39,330 --> 00:39:40,610
and cruel like you?

416
00:39:43,450 --> 00:39:45,290
If you're done with the government work,

417
00:39:45,310 --> 00:39:46,410
then I need to ask you to leave.

418
00:39:47,706 --> 00:39:49,890
You're disturbing my work.

419
00:40:34,312 --> 00:40:36,530
I spent all money.

420
00:40:37,533 --> 00:40:38,610
Phob! You!

421
00:40:39,602 --> 00:40:41,690
It's because of you! You stick your nose where it doesn't belong.

422
00:41:00,578 --> 00:41:02,250
Thank you so much, Sakchai.

423
00:41:02,810 --> 00:41:03,960
No worries.

424
00:41:04,194 --> 00:41:06,570
It is my honor that you decided to ask me for a loan.

425
00:41:18,310 --> 00:41:20,110
You will get your money back soon.

426
00:41:21,269 --> 00:41:22,770
There is no need to hurry.

427
00:41:23,376 --> 00:41:25,970
We're friends and I will help you.

428
00:41:30,130 --> 00:41:31,810
Thank you so much, Sakchai.

429
00:41:32,421 --> 00:41:33,710
Safe travel, Your Highness.

430
00:41:49,693 --> 00:41:53,210
Thank you for inviting me to watch the performance.

431
00:41:54,330 --> 00:41:56,450
You can tell me whether you like it.

432
00:41:56,802 --> 00:41:59,110
I need to see if they're the right choice to perform in the celebration.

433
00:42:09,460 --> 00:42:10,461
Phob!

434
00:42:10,885 --> 00:42:12,370
Tin, Phob is here.

435
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:18,770
Is this Phob?

436
00:42:18,810 --> 00:42:20,370
Long time no see.

437
00:42:21,250 --> 00:42:24,370
Wow! You're a soldier now?

438
00:42:26,293 --> 00:42:27,294
Yes, Your Highness.

439
00:42:27,610 --> 00:42:29,410
It's nice to see you again.

440
00:42:30,530 --> 00:42:31,970
I'm missing the old days,

441
00:42:32,186 --> 00:42:35,050
when Phob lived in the same place as you.

442
00:42:35,397 --> 00:42:39,170
I went to visit you and you were always hanging out with Phob.

443
00:42:47,570 --> 00:42:50,170
You're not going to introduce this beautiful lady?

444
00:42:50,354 --> 00:42:51,770
I am waiting for a while now.

445
00:42:55,202 --> 00:42:57,970
- Right, she is…
- My name is Janthorn.

446
00:42:58,210 --> 00:43:00,250
I'm a journalist at Lok Siam newspaper.

447
00:43:00,485 --> 00:43:02,543
It's nice to meet you, Prince Tinnakorn

448
00:43:02,682 --> 00:43:04,010
and M.R. Ruethaisiri.

449
00:43:05,450 --> 00:43:08,130
Nice to meet you,too, Ms. Janthorn.

450
00:43:09,810 --> 00:43:11,144
You asked me to introduce you

451
00:43:11,640 --> 00:43:13,144
and you introduced yourself first?

452
00:43:13,610 --> 00:43:16,130
I can't wait for you any longer.

453
00:43:16,328 --> 00:43:18,570
You're too slow and we could miss everything.

454
00:43:19,730 --> 00:43:22,970
Hey, I took you here to get a scoop for the celebration.

455
00:43:23,557 --> 00:43:26,210
Fine, don't ask me to do anything for you anymore.

456
00:43:28,784 --> 00:43:30,890
What? A sulking soldier?

457
00:44:34,824 --> 00:44:35,825
No garland

458
00:44:37,010 --> 00:44:38,850
but you can have a cotton rose.

459
00:44:49,638 --> 00:44:51,010
So it means that

460
00:44:51,410 --> 00:44:54,730
you choose me. Is that right?

461
00:45:22,546 --> 00:45:24,170
Why didn't you stay to watch the show?

462
00:45:28,816 --> 00:45:29,930
I'm not feeling well.

463
00:45:33,653 --> 00:45:34,654
Are you sure?

464
00:45:37,301 --> 00:45:39,650
It isn't because of the show reminded you of our past, is it?

465
00:45:40,482 --> 00:45:41,930
That's why you can't stand watching it.

466
00:45:43,240 --> 00:45:45,370
I told you that I forget all about it.

467
00:45:55,213 --> 00:45:56,214
Let me go.

468
00:46:01,730 --> 00:46:02,731
Hey!

469
00:46:25,248 --> 00:46:27,760
Did you and Phob talk about something else besides work?

470
00:46:28,760 --> 00:46:32,200
You can't go soft on him, we still need insight info from Prince Tinnakorn.

471
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:33,960
Phob! Phob!

472
00:46:37,192 --> 00:46:40,008
You wish can never come true.

473
00:46:40,019 --> 00:46:42,120
You are living in a different world from him.

474
00:46:42,152 --> 00:46:44,120
It doesn't have to end up this way.

475
00:46:48,520 --> 00:46:51,300
As for you, your past must be nothing to you.

476
00:46:51,614 --> 00:46:53,120
If that's the case, you should forget about it.

477
00:46:53,720 --> 00:46:54,721
Let me go.

478
00:46:55,840 --> 00:46:57,000
If you want me to let you go,

479
00:46:57,580 --> 00:46:59,280
you need to be more resistant.

